Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Strip @thyme{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; chop leaves until you have @chopped thyme{2%tsp}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, half the chopped thyme, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Pork ==

While veggies roast, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add steak and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Transfer to a second baking sheet.

> Swap in pork tenderloin for steak; cook to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side. Transfer
> to a cutting board to rest for at least 5 minutes.

Roast steak on middle rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and let rest a few minutes, then thinly slice crosswise.

> Skip roasting! Thinly slice steak against the grain.

== Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add onion and remaining chopped thyme. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, @fig jam{1}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until thick and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use ½ cup water and 2 TBSP butter.

== To Serve ==

Divide Brussels sprouts, carrots, and steak between plates. Drizzle pan sauce over steak and serve.